role: I need help with the API

message: How can I help you with the API today?
How do I filter by date?
You can use the date_after or date_before operators in advanced filters. For example: field=created_at&operator=date_after&value=2025-11-01
What endpoints are available?
The API provides endpoints for datasets
response_time: and export. Check /docs for full documentation.

message: How do I export data as JSON?
Use GET /datasets/{name}/export?format=json to export as JSON. You can also use the export endpoint in the UI.
I'm getting a CORS error
CORS errors occur when the API server doesn't allow requests from your origin. Make sure CORS is enabled on the server with your origin in the allowed list.
Can I use regex in filters?
Yes! Use the regex operator in advanced filters. For example: field=email&operator=regex&value=.*@example\.com
How do I bulk update rows?
Use PUT /datasets/{name}/rows/bulk with a JSON body containing an updates array. Each update object needs an id field.
What's the rate limit?
Rate limits vary by endpoint. Most endpoints allow 100-200 requests per minute. Check the X-RateLimit headers in responses.
How do I get dataset metadata?
Use GET /datasets/{name}/metadata to retrieve metadata. Use PUT /datasets/{name}/metadata to update it.
Can I import CSV files?
Yes! Use POST /datasets/{name}/import with a CSV file. Set mode=append to add rows or mode=replace to overwrite.
